{{ speakers_block(speakers) }}
SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
This scene covers the verbal arc around a physical assault:
  1. Pre-incident baseline — tense but controlled argument about the trigger.
  2. Escalation — voices rise; victim is blamed, criticised, demeaned.
  3. Immediate pre-assault — perpetrator gives a final warning or ultimatum.
  4. Assault moment — dialogue breaks; victim reacts vocally (cry, gasp, protest) as assault occurs.
  5. Immediate aftermath — perpetrator justifies or minimises; victim is frightened / in pain.
Note: physical impact sounds will be layered by the acoustic augmenter. This template
generates only spoken utterances and victim vocal reactions.

